President Muhammadu Buhari hailed Governor Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom State on the occasion of his 55th birthday. In a statement signed by Garba Shehu, his spokesman, the President said he is mindful of Emmanuelâ€™s devotion to serving his people. He prayed God Almighty to sustain the Governor with good health and happiness to celebrate more successes in his administration. Buhari urged Emmanuel, who has had successful careers as a banker and chartered accountant before joining politics, not to relent in using his privileged position as an elected public officer holder to move Nigeria forward.